<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>530 and DT-466/408 Diesel Engine Service (1994) - VIBRATION DAMPER, CRANKSHAFT, MAIN BEARINGS, FLYWHEEL AND
        CRANKCASE - INSTALLATION - OIL PAN
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="6">
        <title>OIL PAN</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Prepare oil pan for installation by using a wire wheel to clean RTV from the oil pan lip (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050758">7.58</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ).
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <important>
                    <para>BE SURE TO CLEAN ALL RTV FROM OIL PAN LIP CRANKCASE RAILS, FRONT COVER AND REAR OIL SEAL
                        CARRIER.
                    </para>
                </important>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="ef1050757" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg2396" filename="../figeg2/EG2396.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 7.57.</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Front Cover</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Oil Pick-Up Tube Mounting Bolt</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. Oil Pick-Up Tube</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef1050758" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg2401" filename="../figeg2/EG2401.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 7.58.</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Oil Pan Lip</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Oil Pan</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. Wire Wheel</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install four (4) guide pins/dowels (make locally) into the four corners of the crankcase (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050759">7.59</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">On engines
                <emph type="bold">WITHOUT</emph>
                oil pan mounting bars, use the following procedure:
            </para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Apply1/4 in. (6mm) bead of Wacker T-95 RTV to top ledge of oil pan (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050760">7.60</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Continue applying a 1/4 in. (6mm) bead of Wacker T-95 RTV to grooves located between the
                    rear oil seal carrier and crankcase and between crankcase and rear half of front cover.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Also apply a circle of Wacker T-95 RTV around the cupped plug crankcase orientation
                    holes located on the oil pan rails of the crankcase.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>DO NOT apply RTV more than 5 minutes before installing the oil pan.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Place oil pan onto crankcase. Secure oil pan using eighteen (18) bolts.</para>
                <figure id="ef1050759" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg2398" filename="../figeg2/EG2398.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 7.59.</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. Crankcase</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. Guide Pins</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. Oil PIck-Up Tube</callout1>
                        <callout1>4. Front Cover</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef1050760" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg2399" filename="../figeg2/EG2399.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 7.60.</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. Oil Pan</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. Front Cover</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. RTV Bead</callout1>
                        <callout1>4. Guide Pins</callout1>
                        <callout1>5. Oil Pick-Up Tube</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove four (4) guide dowel pins and replace with four (4) bolts. Tighten all bolts to the
                specified torque value. Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050761">7.61</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">On engines
                <emph type="bold">WITH</emph>
                oil pan mounting bars, use the following procedure:
            </para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Apply a 1/4 in. (6 mm) bead of Wacker T-95 RTV to the following locations (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050762">7.62</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ):
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Where the crankcase and rear half of the front cover and the crankcase and rear oil seal
                    carrier contact each other.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Also apply a circle of Waker T-95 RTV around the cupped plug crankcase orientation holes
                    located on the oil pan rails of the crankcase.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>DO NOT apply RTV more than 5 minutes before installing the oil pan.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Place the oil pan gasket onto the oil pan so that the seal bead of the gasket is TOWARD
                    the crankcase and the edge marked FRONT is facing the fornt cover.
                </para>
                <figure id="ef1050761" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg2400" filename="../figeg2/EG2400.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 7.61.</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. Front Cover</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. Oil Pan Mounting Bolt</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. Oil Pan</callout1>
                        <callout1>4. Crankcase</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef1050762" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg3577" filename="../figeg3/EG3577.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 7.62.</caption>
                </figure>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Place the oil pan onto the crankcase. Place two (2) oil pan mounting bars on the pan oil
                    rail and secure with the ten (10) long mounting bolts. Use the eight (8) shorter bolts to secure the
                    oil pan to the front cover and rear oil seal carrier.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Remove the four (4) guide dowel pins and replace with four (4) bolts. tighten all
                    mounting bolts to the special torque value (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk document="e105_168.xml" xrefid="ef1050763">7.63</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
